[
    {
        "content": "<p>Hi, I want to prove ∫ (t : ℝ) in Set.Icc 0 1, t ^ (α - 1) * (1 - t) ^ (β - 1) = (∫ (x : ℝ) in 0 ..1, ↑x ^ (↑α - 1) * (1 - ↑x) ^ (↑β - 1)).re where α β : ℝ. It seems obvious considering all parameters and variables are real but I stuggle to make it work. I have tried tactics <code>integral_ofReal</code> and <code>congr; rfl</code> to manipulate specific parts of the integrand but little progress. Can someone help? Thank you</p>",
        "id": 521473975,
        "sender_full_name": "Tommy Löfgren",
        "timestamp": 1748723427
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I suggest you start by sharing a <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mwe.html\">#mwe</a></p>",
