    {
        "content": "<p>So I want to show this (is this same as sharing a <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mwe.html\">#mwe</a>, I'm new here?) \"<code>\nexample {α β : ℝ} (h1: 0 &lt; α) (h2 : 0 &lt; β) : ∫ (t : ℝ) in Set.Icc 0 1, t ^ (α - 1) * (1 - t) ^ (β - 1) = \n(∫ (x : ℝ) in 0 ..1, ↑x ^ (↑α - 1) * (1 - ↑x) ^ (↑β - 1)).re := by\n    sorry\n</code>\" which I have derived without errors inside a lemma. However now when trying to state it as a separate example, copying it from my InfoView, I get an error at \"unexpected token; expected ',' or '..' Lean 4\" around the 1 in \"<code>∫ (x : ℝ) in 0 ..1,</code>\". I have ended up in this situation when combining theorems from Complex with real variables.</p>",
        "id": 521475879,
        "sender_full_name": "Tommy Löfgren",
        "timestamp": 1748725207
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mwe.html\">#mwe</a> is a link, did you read it? In particular to post code you need to use <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib/wiki/Code-in-backticks\">#backticks</a> (also a link)</p>",
